  • Method Details

    • decorate

      public static java.lang.String decorate​(java.lang.String val)
      Parameters:
      val - String that you want to store as CSV
      Returns:
      String with all of the formating needed
      Brief:
      Formats the string so it can be used as a CSV cell. String is quoted if it has quotes or commas. All of the quotes are duplicated ie " -> "".
      Warning:
      This function doesn't add commas, so do that yourself.

    • undecorate

      public static java.lang.String undecorate​(java.lang.String val)
      Parameters:
      val - String that represents CSV cell with or without leading comma.
      Returns:
      String that is stored in the CSV cell.
      Brief:
      String all of the CSV specific stuff. See the decorate function to learn more.
      Warning:
      This function assumes that the comma either not present or leading.

    • nextCell

      public static java.lang.String nextCell​(java.lang.String val, int offset)
      Parameters:
      val - String to parse.
      offset - Offset into the val
      Returns:
      String that represents a single cell
      Brief:
      Find the string that represents a single cell in a multi-cell input string with a known offset from the start.
      Usage:
      Add length of the returned string to the offset to parse the next cell
